7 (a) There is appropriated three million dollars
8 ($3,000,000.00) from the legislative stabilization reserve account
9 to the department of environmental quality to execute contracts or
10 provide grants to the city of Rock Springs or Sweetwater county
11 for the cost of segment two (2) of the Bitter Creek revitalization
12 project. Expenditure of this appropriation is conditioned on
13 matching funds in the ratio of one dollar ($1.00) of appropriated
14 funds from the legislative stabilization reserve account to not
15 less than one dollar ($1.00) of matching funds from the city of
16 Rock Springs or Sweetwater county. Matching funds shall be acquired
17 by the city of Rock Springs or Sweetwater county before any funds
18 from the legislative stabilization reserve account are expended
19 pursuant to this subsection.
20
21 (b) The department of environmental quality shall submit new
22 grant applications or modify existing grant applications to the
23 federal office of surface mining to secure qualifying federal funds
24 for this project. The appropriation of legislative stabilization
25 reserve account funds in this section shall be reduced by one
26 dollar ($1.00) of legislative stabilization reserve account funds
27 for each one dollar ($1.00) of federal funds applied for and
28 received after the date of enactment of this act for the project
29 in this section.
30
31 (c) Notwithstanding W.S. 9-2-1008 and 9-4-207, any
32 unexpended, unobligated funds from this appropriation shall not
33 revert until June 30, 2029.".
